    <updated>20251014T090749Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Consistent with sialolithiasis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows lamellated calculi consistent with sialolithiasis.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>CAI (squamous mucosa)</title>
    <created>20180727T065101Z</created>
    <updated>20230608T032145Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>chronic active inflammation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows squamous mucosal tissue with acute and chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the underlying stroma. </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>cemento-osseous dysplasia / cementoma</title>
    <created>20180316T055619Z</created>
    <updated>20180316T060151Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Benign </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">fibroosseous lesion (see NOTE).</span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="line-height: 1.45;">Microscopic description:</span><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Section shows spicules of bone in a fibrous background.</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;"><br/></span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">NOTE:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">Taken together, this is a benign fibroosseous lesion, </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">which can be consistent with cemento-osseous dysplasia </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">(cementoma). Clinical and radiographic correlation is </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">required for the diagnosis.</span></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
