<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Cholesteatoma</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows laminated keratin consistent with cholesteatoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>    <span>    </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>CHR</title>
    <created>20170117T010606Z</created>
    <updated>20260320T053450Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Chronic hypertrophic rhinitis, bilateral inferior turbinates, submucosal turbinectomy</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>Chronic hypertrophic rhinitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The turbinate tissue shows stromal edema, vascular proliferation and glandular hyperplasia as well as lymphocytic and eosinophilic cells infiltration.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);">Eosinophil count per high power field: </span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>CHR NSD</title>
    <created>20180503T065554Z</created>
    <updated>20260605T031033Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Chronic rhinitis with polypoid change and clinically nasal septal deviation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section of the turbinates reveal marked stromal edema, vascular proliferation and glandular hyperplasia as well as lymphocytic and eosinophilic cells infiltration.</div><div>Strip of hyaline cartilage is consistent with septal cartilage.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);">Eosinophil count per high power field: </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>CHR NSD &amp; CPS</title>
    <created>20170420T072321Z</created>
    <updated>20230616T060734Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>1. Chronic rhinitis with polypoid change and clinically nasal septal deviation, bilateral inferior turbinates and nasal septum, septomeatoplasty</div><div>2. Chronic sinusitis with polypoid change, bilateral paranasal sinuses, multiple sinusectomy</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>GROSS DESCRIPTION:</div><div>1. The specimen is composed of ___ fragments of turbinate tissue measuring up to ___ x</div><div>   ___ x ___ cm, ___ fragments of bony tissue measuring up to ___ x ___ x ___ cm, and</div><div>   ___ fragment of septal cartilage measuring ___ x ___ x ___ cm. (RA)</div><div><br/></div><div>2. The specimen is composed of multiple pieces of soft tissue measuring up to ___ x ___</div><div>   x ___ cm and multiple pieces of bony tissue measuring up to ___ x ___ x ___ cm. (RB)</div><div><br/></div><div>Representative sections are submitted in two cassettes.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>MICROSCOPIC DESCRIPTION:</div><div>1. Section of the turbinates reveal marked stromal edema, vascular proliferation and</div><div>   glandular hyperplasia as well as lymphocytic and eosinophilic cells infiltration.</div><div>   No evidence of malignancy.</div><div>   Strip of hyaline cartilage is consistent with septal cartilage.</div><div><br/></div><div>2. The sinus mucosal tissue shows glandular proliferation, marked stromal edema, lymphocytic</div><div>   and eosinophilic inflammation. No evidence of malignancy.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);">Eosinophil count per high power field: </span></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>chronic active</title>
    <created>20240426T063413Z</created>
    <updated>20240426T063458Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>chronic active tonsillitis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The lymphoid tissues exhibit increased numbers of lymphoid</div><div>follicles and germinal center formation, associated with</div><div>stromal congestion and plasma cell infiltration,</div><div>suppurative inflammation of the epithelial crypts, and</div><div>focal epithelial ulceration. No evidence of malignancy is</div><div>observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Chronic rhinitis with polypoid change and clinically nasal septal deviation, bilateral inferior turbinates and nasal septum, septomeatoplasty</title>
    <created>20170117T011616Z</created>
    <updated>20230713T063450Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section of the turbinates reveal marked stromal edema, vascular proliferation and </div><div>glandular hyperplasia as well as lymphocytic and eosinophilic cells infiltration. No </div><div>evidence of malignancy. </div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);">Eosinophil count per high power field: </span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div>Strip of hyaline cartilage is consistent with septal cartilage. </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>chronic sialadenitis</title>
    <created>20161117T023244Z</created>
    <updated>20230825T081138Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><font face="Harlow Solid Italic">chronic sialadenitis.</font></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><font face="Harlow Solid Italic"><br/></font></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><font face="Harlow Solid Italic">Microscopic description:</font></span></div><div><span style="font-size: 16px;"><font face="Harlow Solid Italic">It shows lobules of salivary acini with interstitial fibrosis and marked lymphoplasmacytic infiltration featuring lymphoid follicles formation and leading to atrophy and loss of acini. Microliths are also noted.</font></span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Chronic sialadenitis with Sialolithiasis (r/o IgG4-related disease)</title>
    <created>20161117T023255Z</created>
    <updated>20180608T074829Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="font-family:gotham, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;font-size:14px;"><span style="font-family: &quot;times new roman&quot;, times, serif;">Sections show lobules of salivary acini with interstitial fibrosis and marked 
lymphoplasmacytic infiltration as well as occasional neutrophils and eosinophils, 
</span></div><div style="font-family:&quot;times new roman&quot;, times, serif;font-size:14px;">leading to atrophy and loss of acini. Microliths are also noted. No malignancy is 
observed. There is no elevated IgG4:IgG ratio of plasma cells in this tissue as 
demonstrated by immunohistochemical stains, excluding IgG4-related disease.
</div><div style="font-family:&quot;times new roman&quot;, times, serif;font-size:14px;">Four lymph nodes are seen with preserved nodal architecture. 
</div><div style="font-family:&quot;times new roman&quot;, times, serif;font-size:14px;"><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Chronic tonsillitis</title>
    <created>20180720T044540Z</created>
    <updated>20260417T081927Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Chronic tonsillitis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The lymphoid tissues exhibit increased numbers of lymphoid follicles and germinal center formation, associated with stromal congestion and plasma cell infiltration, fibrinopurulent collection in the epithelial crypts, and focal epithelial ulceration. No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>COM</title>
    <created>20170425T042056Z</created>
    <updated>20230921T072832Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Consistent with chronic otitis media.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The covering squamous epithelium is eroded focally and the</div><div>underlying fibrous tissue shows chronic inflammation,</div><div>fibrosis and vascular dilation.        </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>COM+cholesteatoma</title>
    <created>20170420T072356Z</created>
    <updated>20230921T072842Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>right/left middle ear, tympanoplasty with mastoidectomy --- </div><div>chronic otitis media with cholesteatoma</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>The section shows soft tissue with chronic inflammation and laminated keratin consistent with chronic otitis media with cholesteatoma.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Confirmed, adenoids, adenoidectomy</title>
    <created>20161208T090629Z</created>
    <updated>20260316T030254Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Confirmed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>It shows benign epithelium and lymphoid stroma.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
