  <note>
    <title>consistent with nasopalatine duct cyst, inflamed.</title>
    <created>20190813T045502Z</created>
    <updated>20240926T060955Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>consistent with<a href="evernote:///view/26224745/s227/a6778895-cae8-4b47-9ca4-e68ccad6d59e#9d10b55d-6d01-460d-a98b-83b61bbb5c1b/b011427c-42ab-4073-a613-9784cfb9d08d/" rev="en_rl_none"> nasopalatine duct cyst,</a> inflamed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows cystic lesion with diffuse infiltrate of neutrophils, and lymphoplasmacytic cells. Focal lining of</div><div>stratified squamous epithelium is seen. Fragmented bony spicules are also seen. The findings are are consistent but not pathognomonic for nasopalatine duct cyst. Clinico-radiological correlation is mandatory for the diagnosis. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
