  <note>
    <title>CPS</title>
    <created>20170216T083343Z</created>
    <updated>20250425T051416Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Chronic sinusitis with polypoid change.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The sinus mucosal tissue shows glandular proliferation, marked stromal edema, lymphocytic</div><div>and eosinophilic infiltration. No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);">Eosinophil count per high power field: </span></div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);"><span style="--en-markholder:true;"><br/></span></span></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The sinus mucosal tissues show glandular proliferation, marked stromal edema, lymphocytic and eosinophilic infiltration. Some mucoid and eosinophilic</div><div>exudate is noted. No fungus is identified by PAS. No evidence of malignancy is  noted.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);">Eosinophil count per high power field: </span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>CRS Chronic rhinosinusitis</title>
    <created>20240525T054801Z</created>
    <updated>20241119T080811Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div> </div><div>Chronic rhinosinusitis</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows submucosal edematous stroma with vascular proliferation and glandular hyperplasia, and admixture of acute and chronic inflammatory cells including increase in eosinophils.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="color:rgb(33, 33, 33);">Eosinophil count per high power field: </span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210728T081021Z</created>
    <updated>20231201T091126Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Dental lamina rests.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows fibrous tissue containing odontogenic</div><div>epithelium. It is most consistent with dental lamina rests.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>dentigerous cyst.</title>
    <created>20190130T045550Z</created>
    <updated>20250611T080327Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Consistent with dentigerous cyst.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show fibrous tissue focally lined by nonkeratinizing squamous epithelium with mild chronic inflammatory infiltrate in the fibrous wall. No malignancy is observed.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div><hr/><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Consistent with dentigerous cyst.</span></div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show fibrous tissue focally lined by nonkeratinizing squamous epithelium with odontogenic epithelial rests within the cystic wall. No malignancy is observed.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
