      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>fistula, consistent with first branchial cleft anomaly.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: &quot;Microsoft YaHei&quot;;">Section shows a cyst lined by squamous epithelium </span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">containing keratin materials, which is</span> <span style="line-height: 1.45;">consistent with first branchial cleft</span> <span style="line-height: 1.45;">anomaly</span><span style="line-height: 1.45;">.</span></div><div><br style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Fistula, consistent with first branchial cleft anomaly. Cartilage</title>
    <created>20180308T063852Z</created>
    <updated>20250227T061758Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">Fistula, </span>consistent with first branchial cleft anomaly.</div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">Section shows a fistulous tract lined by squamous epithelium </span>containing keratin materials. Cartilage is identified in the <span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">immediately associated tissue. Focal granulation tissue with </span>chronic inflammation and multinucleated giant cells <span style="font-family: 'Microsoft YaHei';">aggregate are seen. These pathological pictures are </span>consistent with first branchial cleft <span style="font-family: Microsoft YaHei;">anomaly</span>.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20180831T031648Z</created>
    <updated>20240808T050012Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="padding-left:40px;">granulation tissue.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;"><br/></div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Microscopic description:</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">Section shows cystic lesion lined by granulation tissue accompanied by acute and chronic inflammatory infiltrate. No malignancy is observed.</div><div style="padding-left:40px;">                            </div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Head and neck</title>
    <created>20141001T083649Z</created>
    <updated>20230713T063415Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(0, 0, 255); font-family: gotham;"><br/></span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; color: rgb(0, 0, 255); font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">exostosis.</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: gotham;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Sections show dense lamellated cortical bone fragments with small marrow spaces filled with fat and loose fibrovascular stroma. No malignancy is observed.</span></div></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">Nasal polyp</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"><span style="font-size: 12px; font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The polyp is lined by respiratory epithelium exhibiting focal squamous metaplasia and thickening of the basement membrane. The underlying stroma appears loose and mucoid, with intact mucous glands and mixed inflammatory cell infiltrates. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br clear="none" /></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;"></div><div style="margin-top: 1em;margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><span style="font-size: 12px;">Pleomorphic adenoma (Mixed tumor), salivary gland, 2013100625; 2014040839</span></div><div style="padding-left: 30px;margin-top: 1em;margin-bottom: 1em;-en-paragraph:true;"><span style="font-size: 12px;">It shows lobules of salivary gland acini and one demarcated tumor composed of bland-looking mononuclear cells featuring plasmacytoid appearance focally and arranged in sheets and occasionally tubules, in fibromyxoid, hyalinized or lipomatous stroma. (Infarction is present focally.)</span></div><div><br clear="none" /></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Inverted Schneiderian papilloma</title>
    <created>20170109T084912Z</created>
    <updated>20260210T071704Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sinonasal papilloma, inverted type.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows endophytic growth of thickened epithelial nests arising from the surface repiratory epithelium.</div><div><span style="color:rgb(0, 0, 0);">Transmigrating neutrophils and neutrophilic microabscesses are seen.</span></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20210106T074418Z</created>
    <updated>20231117T062550Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>keratin materials with fungal infestation.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows keratin materials admixed with some fungal</div><div>spores which are highlighted by PAS stain.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>keratosis obturans</title>
    <created>20230706T052736Z</created>
    <updated>20230706T052922Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>keratosis obturans</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows layers of anucleated squames. </div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>*young adult</div><div>*usually bilateral</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>lymphangiomatous polyp</title>
    <created>20240412T035521Z</created>
    <updated>20240412T035641Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>lymphangiomatous polyp</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows polypoid tissue lined by respiratory</div><div>epithelium with dilated lymphatic channels containing clear</div><div>and proteinaceous fluid. Mixed inflammatory infiltrate is</div><div>also seen. Immunohistochemically, the endothelial cells</div><div>lining the lymphatic channels are positive for D2-40 but not</div><div>GFAP and S100.</div><div>No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Lymphocytic thyroiditis (thyroid)</title>
    <created>20170117T011756Z</created>
    <updated>20230608T032139Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Lymphocytic thyroiditis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>There is lymphocytic infiltrate in the stroma with lymphoid follicles formation and focal prominent germinal centers, accompanied by fibrosis and atrophy of follicular epithelium.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>There is diffuse involvement of the thyroid by a prominent lymphocytic infiltrate, including associated germinal center present in and around the thyroid parenchyma. Oncocytic change of follicular cells and fibrosis are also seen.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>未命名記事</title>
    <created>20170725T064951Z</created>
    <updated>20250224T014301Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>lymphoid hyperplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The covering respiratory epithelium shows squamous metaplasia and appears to be intact and lacks any cellular atypia. The underlying lymphoid stroma shows proliferation of lymphoid tissue with germinal center formation. </div><div>No invasive carcinoma is demonstrated by AE1/AE3.</div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div>No evidence of tumor cell infiltration is identified in this section.</div><hr/><div>Lymphoid hyperplasia.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The covering respiratory epithelium shows squamous metaplasia and appears to be intact and lacks any cellular atypia. The underlying lymphoid stroma shows proliferation of lymphoid tissue with germinal center formation. </div><div>Immunohistochemically, CD3 and CD20 demonstrate normal distribution of T and B lymphocytes. </div><div>The lymphoid cells of germinal center are negative for bcl-2.</div><div>No invasive carcinoma is demonstrated by AE1/AE3.</div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Medullary carcinoma</title>
    <created>20200505T045708Z</created>
    <updated>20200505T050101Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Medullary carcinoma.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections shows tumor cells bearing round to oval, plasmacytoid appearance with stippled, fine nuclear chromatin, accompanied by amyloid</div><div>stromal accumulation (demonstrated by Congo red, which shows apple-green birefringence under polarized light).</div><div><br/></div><div>Immunohistochemically, the tumor cells are positive for synaptophysin and TTF-1 but not thyroglobulin.</div><div><br/></div><div>(This case has been peer reviewed by two doctors.)<br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Metastatic SCC, neck soft tissue</title>
    <created>20170216T081930Z</created>
    <updated>20170412T125401Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Sections show soft tissue infiltrated by neoplastic squamous cells with invasion into skeletal muscle fibers. The metastatic focus measure _ cm. Although no  residual lymphoid tissue is discernible, this metastatic lesion might represent a nodal metastasis with totally destroyed nodal architecture.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>migraine surgery</title>
    <created>20210914T060127Z</created>
    <updated>20210914T060248Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>Auriculotemporal nerve, bilateral, migraine surgery ---</div><div>confirmed.</div><div><br/></div><div>Gross description:</div><div>The specimen consists of multiple pieces of tissue</div><div>measuring up to 0.5x0.3x0.1 cm.</div><div><br/></div><div>All for section.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Sections show vessels and nerve bundles in fibroadipose tissue.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>mucocele 2</title>
    <created>20190314T075154Z</created>
    <updated>20230713T064307Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>mucocele.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows squamous mucosal tissue with mucin-filled cyst</div><div>lined by cuboidal epitehlial cells. Associated mixed</div><div>inflammatory infiltrate is seen in adjacent tissue.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Mucous retention cyst (Sinus)</title>
