    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Consistent with torus mandibularis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows bony fragments consistent with torus</div><div>mandibularis.</div><div>    </div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>UA unicystic ameloblastoma</title>
    <created>20200226T025840Z</created>
    <updated>20230525T091648Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows cystic spaces lined by odontogenic epithelium</div><div>with focal evidence of ameloblastic change, including</div><div>palisading basal cells with reverse polarity and</div><div>subnuclear vacuoles.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>UPPP</title>
    <created>20170215T083351Z</created>
    <updated>20251219T053719Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div style="padding-left:40px;">1.  Chronic hypertrophic tonsillitis, bilateral palatine tonsils;</div><div>2. Vascular congestion and tissue edema, uvula;</div><div>uvulopalatopharyngoplasty (UPPP)</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><ol><li><div>The lymphoid tissues exhibit increased numbers of lymphoid follicles and germinal center formation, associated with stromal congestion and plasma cell infiltration, fibrinopurulent collection in the epithelial crypts, and focal epithelial ulceration. <span style="color:rgb(251, 95, 44);">Masses of Actinomyces are also noted.</span> No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div></li><li><div>The slide (B) represents a loose fibrous connective tissue which exhibits vascular congestion as well as tissue edema. The overlying squamous mucosa is unremarkable.</div></li></ol><div>        </div><div>    </div><hr/><div>PATHOLOGIC DIAGNOSIS:</div><div>uvulopalatopharyngoplasty (UPPP) --- Chronic hypertrophic tonsillitis.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>The lymphoid tissues exhibit increased numbers of lymphoid follicles and germinal center formation, associated with stromal congestion and plasma cell infiltration, fibrinopurulent collection in the epithelial crypts, and focal epithelial ulceration. Masses of Actinomyces are also noted. No evidence of malignancy is observed.</div><hr/><div>uvulopalatopharyngoplasty (UPPP) --- vascular congestion and tissue edema.</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div>Section shows squamous mucosal tissue which exhibits vascular congestion as well as tissue edema. The overlying squamous mucosa is unremarkable.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Vascular congestion and tissue edema, uvula and soft palate, excision (spleep apnea)</title>
    <created>20170215T082642Z</created>
    <updated>20170215T082714Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div><br/></div><div>The slide represents a loose fibrous connective tissue which exhibits vascular congestion as well as tissue edema.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Vocal cord polyp</title>
    <created>20170206T060243Z</created>
    <updated>20240311T024425Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="margin-top:16px;"><span style="font-family: gotham;">Vocal cord polyp.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">The slide shows polypoid lesion covered by stratified squamous epithelium supported by loose and edematous hypocellular stroma. There is no evidence of malignancy.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">vocal cord polyp.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-family: gotham;">Microscopic description:</span></div><div>Section shows <span style="font-family: gotham, helvetica, sans-serif;">polypoid lesion covered by stratified squamous epithelium with </span>dilated venous channels and extravasated fibrin within the lamina propria.</div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Vocal cyst</title>
    <created>20170217T025611Z</created>
    <updated>20170217T025621Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Section shows bland-looking stratified squamous epithelium supported by fibrous stroma. Separated pieces of tissue with myxoid matrix are noted. There is no evidence of malignancy.</div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Warthin tumor</title>
    <created>20170213T023148Z</created>
    <updated>20250701T023659Z</updated>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Elaine huang</author>
      <source>desktop.win</source>
      <source-application>evernote.win32</source-application>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div style="display:none;--en-chs:&quot;&quot;"> </div><div>Warthin's tumor</div><div><br/></div><div>Microscopic description:</div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;">Section shows lobules of salivary gland acini with a demarcated tumor composed of cystic spaces and papillary structures lined by oncocytic luminal cells and cuboidal basal cells, in a prominent lymphoid stroma. The lumina of cysts contains thick secretions, cholesteral crystals and</span></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;">cellular debris. Focal mucinous metaplasia is seen. No malignancy is observed.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><span style="font-size: 12px;">_ lymph nodes with preserved nodal architectures are also identified in adjacent soft tissue.</span></div><div><br/></div><div><br/></div></en-note>      ]]>
    </content>
  </note>
